> After we tested this at the Fresh Farm, a lot of people said it was great with a hard boiled egg added at the end. If you have some eggs, then go for it!

Pre-heat your #oven{} to 200 degrees. Chop the @sweet potato{3/4} into 1cm cubes. Toss the sweet potatoes in @oil{1%tbsp} and @salt{1/2%tsp}. Lay on a #baking tray{} and cook in your oven for ~{20-25%minutes}.

Roughly chop the @baby spinach{1/2} leaves and the @coriander{2}. 

> You can also cut spinach and coriander with scissors to save some time.

Peel the @carrot{1} and chop into tiny 1/2cm cubes.

Remove the core from the peppers and chop half of the @yellow pepper{1} into 1/2cm cubes and the other half into 1cm cubes. Toss the 1cm pepper cubes in @olive oil{2%tsp} and roast with the sweet potatoes for the last ~{10%minutes}.

Cut the @halloumi{1} into 1cm thick slices. Coat in the @harissa spice mix{3/4}. Heat a #large frying pan{} with @oil{1 1/2%tbsp}. Fry off the halloumi for ~{2-3%minutes} on each side, until golden brown.

Place your carrot, 1/2cm pepper cubes and spinach into a #bowl{}. Chop your fried halloumi into 20 pence-sized pieces and toss this into your #salad bowl{} with your roasted sweet potato, pepper and coriander.

Mix @olive oil{6%tbsp} and the zest and juice of the @lemon{1/2} in a bowl. Add @salt{1/2%tsp} and a good pinch of @pepper{pinch}, mix together and put to the side.

> To get more juice from your lemon roll it firmly between the palm of your hand and the chopping board before cutting it in half, sticking a fork into it and squeezing.

Take your salad to the table and drizzle over your dressing. Toss everything together really well.

Taste a mouthful for seasoning and add a bit more salt and pepper until it's just right.